The cast of 'Dream: The Lebo Mathosa Story' pose for a picture ahead of the premier of the docu-series. JOHANNESBURG - Dream: The Lebo Mathosa story received mixed reviews from social media users after it premiered on BET Africa on Wednesday night. READ: KB to star as Lebo Mathosa in upcoming biopic The six part docu-series stars singer and actress Keabetswe “KB” Motsililanyane as the lead role of adult Mathosa along side Somizi Mhlongo's daughter, Bahumi Madisakwane, as her younger counterpart. Many people said the first episode was too confusing, while others applauded the star-studded cast for the excellent execution of the storyline.